<div style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">
  <h1 style="color: #17a2b8;">Simple API Page</h1>
  <p>This page simulates a simple API endpoint with basic data.</p>

  <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 30px;">
    
    <section style="border: 1px solid #17a2b8; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; background-color: #d1ecf1;">
      <h3>API Response Data</h3>
      <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; font-family: monospace;">
        <pre style="margin: 0; white-space: pre-wrap;"><%= JSON.pretty_generate(@data) %></pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section style="border: 1px solid #17a2b8; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; background-color: #d1ecf1;">
      <h3>API Information</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Response Format:</strong> JSON</li>
        <li><strong>Query Complexity:</strong> Simple</li>
        <li><strong>Database Operations:</strong> Basic COUNT queries</li>
        <li><strong>Expected Performance:</strong> Fast</li>
      </ul>
      
      <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
        <h4>API Endpoints:</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><%= link_to "JSON Response", api_simple_path(format: :json), style: "color: #17a2b8;" %></li>
          <li><%= link_to "HTML View", api_simple_path, style: "color: #17a2b8;" %></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

  <div style="margin-top: 30px; padding: 20px; background-color: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px;">
    <h3>About This Page</h3>
    <p>
      This page demonstrates a <strong>simple API endpoint</strong> that returns basic statistics 
      using fast COUNT queries. It supports both HTML and JSON responses and should generate 
      minimal database load in Rails Pulse monitoring.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Tip:</strong> Add <code>.json</code> to the URL to see the JSON response format.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>